<Link id="l00259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="259"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Provides a lazy, caching interface for making common memory aliasing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00260" /><CodeLine lineNumber="260"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// information queries, backed by LLVM&#39;s alias analysis passes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00261" /><CodeLine lineNumber="261"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00262" /><CodeLine lineNumber="262"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The dependency information returned is somewhat unusual, but is pragmatic.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="263"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// If queried about a store or call that might modify memory, the analysis</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="264"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// will return the instruction&#91;s&#93; that may either load from that memory or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="265"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// store to it.  If queried with a load or call that can never modify memory,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="266"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the analysis will return calls and stores that might modify the pointer,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00267" /><CodeLine lineNumber="267"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// but generally does not return loads unless a) they are volatile, or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00268" /><CodeLine lineNumber="268"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// b) they load from &#42;must-aliased&#42; pointers.  Returning a dependence on</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00269" /><CodeLine lineNumber="269"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// must-alias&#39;d pointers instead of all pointers interacts well with the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00270" /><CodeLine lineNumber="270"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// internal caching mechanism.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00271" /><CodeLine lineNumber="271" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorydependenceresults"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorydependenceresults/#a2d532144bcebb13e2fbe5db3dee77abf">MemoryDependenceResults</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
